Based on my research, the latest MSTest is **v4.2.2** (a major version bump from your 3.8.0). Here are the breaking changes that affect **your code specifically**:

---

## 1. `[ExpectedException]` is removed (compile error)

This is the biggest impact. Your two test methods using `[ExpectedException(typeof(...))]` will fail to compile. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

## 2. `Assert.IsTrue(true)` triggers warning MSTEST0032

The analyzer severity was bumped from Info → **Warning** in v4. Your `Assert.IsTrue(true)` in `Validate_ValidInput_Succeeds` will produce a build warning (or error if you use `TreatWarningsAsErrors`).

---

## Other v4 breaking changes (not hitting your code today, but worth knowing):

| Change | Impact |
|--------|--------|
| `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` | Only if you have custom test method attributes |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Only if you specify `EndOfClass` explicitly |
| `TestContext.Properties` is now `IDictionary<string, object>` | Only if you use `.Contains()` on it |
| `Assert` message+params APIs simplified | Only if you pass `object[]` format args |
| .NET 7 and below dropped | You're on net8.0, so you're fine |

---

Would you like me to upgrade the project and fix the code?
